labels.label:
Define request to send to Livy.
"file" is the path of the algorithm you want to use. "args" is an array with two elements. The first one is the path where to retrieve the input file. The second is the path where to save the output of the algorithm.
Example: {"file": "hdfs://hadoop-namenode:9014/algorithms/classifier-spark.py", "args": ["http://hadoop-namenode:9870/webhdfs/v1${path}/${filename}?op=OPEN", "/output/${now():toNumber():append("_label.json")}"]}
